Moving forward, beyond Kaine's teleprompter Spanglish, the clown car of bought and paid for Clintonite pundits, and the megadata vaccumed from "internet of feelings" Ohio's governor Kasich will finally get active in the zone to help Donnie pull out the win just before race hits home stretch. He is more dynamic and can reach across party lines beter than Kaine, who is awkward insider, and preaches to the choir as a former Democratic National Committee boss. Pence will shape shift into a more aggyessive campaigner to avoid getting "Quayled" by Dem controlled anti-Trump media. Clinton camp made big tactical error by not choosing Vilsack as VP. Also, recent "tweaking" of polls (favoring Hillary mostly) makes the pollsters a new target for "populists" of all stripes. Ditto softening of "margin of error" to remove "error." My intention is not to promote Trump here, but to note the general devolution of the campaign process. Ohio is still the ultimate swing state and Kasich (although a Steeler fan;) will play big in the red zone.
Trump could pull this off dependent on turn out and registration of the white non college demographic, the same demographic that is influencing voter results in Europe
